&lt;salute&gt;</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wynterwolf  Crow Darkstalker</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/2/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>11:05:52 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=370.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">... and then there was none.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Crow stood over the dust shrouded body of a hugh barbarian warrior resting on a crudly carved stone dais. The warrior's remains dressed in mismatched items of armor ... his weapons, a tomahawk and bladed claws, resting by his side. A faint sheen of magical energy encased the body keeping it alive and whole incase the spirit should ever return to once again bring life to it. Crow's eyes began to mist over as he looked at the shell of flesh that he once was and then looked towards a rune carved doorway across the cave. Looking through the magical portal was like peering through several feet of murky water, but he watched as his old friends from a far off land gather in a moment of silent reflection. Each in turn steped forward to say there own private good-byes to a battle hardened Paladin. Lord Airrlan. Walking slowly forward, Crow found himself standing with his nose almost touching the surface of the portal, but a soft brush of his finger tips confirmed his suspicions ... he couldn't go through. He stood for what seemed an eternity as members of the Forgotten Truth, both new and old, came forward to say their farewells until eventually there were no more. Crow turned away from the doorway as his friend faded from site but remembers back over time and space to the stinking, rat infested tunnels under the city of Qeynos in far off Norrath. There, one night, 3 young adventures met and formed a plan to shake the very pillars of Norrath. They would form a guild that no other would rival based on their own strengths. The morality of the shining Paladin, the mystic arts of the Mage, ad the ferocity and honor of the Barbarian Warrior. Glancing at the body of the warrior on the dais, Crow remembered the days that he had inhabited that very same body, the day he met Airrlan and Dabez and the day that the Forgotten Truth was formed. Wynterwolf was the first to leave in search of his own life in far off Dereth. Now Lord Airrlan was gone and Dabez had not been heard of in months. Truly, this was a sad day as the end to a chapter had been reached. Who knew what would transpire in the months and years to follow, but it would never be the same. Reaching under his shirt, Crow grasped the cold metal disk that lay on his chest. A quick jerk snapped the thin, rawhide cord from which the object dangled. Opening his hands, Crow gazed apon the gold piece stamped with the city mark of Qeynos. Flipping it over, melted into the surface by controlled mage fire, were the initials FT. Burned their years ago by the young mage Dabez, only 2 others were in existence. One with Airrlan and one with Dabez. Somehow it just didn't feel right wearing it anymore. Walking to his old body, Crow laid the coin on the chest of the warrior and watched as it slowly sank through the mystic shield to come to rest on the armor covered figure. He then turned and walked slowly from the cave, never to look back. It truly was the end of a chapter.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/bl